{"tid":2193269,"cid":5,"subCid":12,"title":"原來英國可以民主投票選舉 Police and Crime Commissioner ！","createTime":"2020-09-07T16:33:38.000Z","updateTime":"2020-09-08T15:02:56.000Z","uid":79563,"like":0,"dislike":2,"uniUserReply":2,"replies":[{"pid":"51eb4f5c7f4ba32e42565066c8b44008f0ca779f","tid":2193269,"uid":79563,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-09-07T16:33:38.000Z","msg":"Police and Crime Commissioner 有乜權力?<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/elections-in-the-uk/police-and-crime-commissioner\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gov.uk%2Felections-in-the-uk%2Fpolice-and-crime-commissioner&d=nUkjSwirbxPTmroveKClqLyGpUrO7QrNXIpVIwIXQug%3D&h=facf9c39\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.gov.uk/elections-in-the-uk/police-and-crime-commissioner</a><br />\n<br />\nThere are 41 Police and Crime Commissioners (PCCs) in England and Wales who are elected to make sure the police are run properly. There is no elected PCC for London.<br />\n<br />\nTo vote in a PCC election you must:<br />\n<br />\nbe registered to vote<br />\nbe 18 or over on the day of the election (&lsquo;polling day&rsquo;)<br />\nbe a British, Irish, Commonwealth or EU citizen<br />\nbe resident at an address in England or Wales (excluding London)<br />\nnot be legally excluded from voting<br />\nPCCs are elected using the Supplementary Vote system. You make a first and second choice when you vote.<br />\n<br />\nIf no candidate gets more than 50% of the first choice votes, all except the top 2 candidates are eliminated. If your first choice candidate is eliminated, and your second choice is for one of the top 2, your second choice is counted."},{"pid":"285ff138fb463d08e67b15bd7730939c62daf7fa","tid":2193269,"uid":79563,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-09-08T02:46:04.000Z","msg":"Police and Crime Commissioner 有乜職權？"},{"pid":"0448c734f5b75ff92c0103d155bc3e5af1ea0a52","tid":2193269,"uid":33263,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1